  "text": "The concept of creative self-efficacy is supported by [CITATION_1] self-efficacy theory, which describes self-confidence and beliefs about the self in terms of having the required knowledge, skill and ability to perform a specific task. Creative self-efficacy, therefore, is the degree to which a person displays confidence in solving problems creatively [CITATION_2] . Previous studies have linked self-efficacy to creative behaviour in individuals [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
